---
description: Keep compose.yml and generate-env.sh in sync when backend env vars change
alwaysApply: true
---

# Backend environment variables

Whenever you **add, rename, change the default of, or remove** an environment variable used by the backend (including `os.getenv` / `os.environ` reads and compose-injected vars):

1. Update [`compose.yml`](compose.yml) — pass the var into the correct service’s `environment:` (usually `backend`). Prefer `${NAME:-default}` when a local default is safe.
2. Update [`scripts/generate-env.sh`](scripts/generate-env.sh) — add/remove/adjust the matching line in `_ENV_TEMPLATE` (static default, empty value, `<set>`, or `<gen:…>` as appropriate).

Do this in the **same change** as the code that introduces or drops the variable. Do not leave compose / generate-env out of date.

```bash
# ❌ BAD — only read in Python
os.getenv("MY_NEW_FLAG")

# ✅ GOOD — Python + compose.yml environment + generate-env.sh _ENV_TEMPLATE
```

Secrets: never hardcode real secrets in compose or the template; use `${NAME}` / empty / `<set>` and document intended defaults only.
